choices.text: the discovery of gold. The discovery of gold in Australia was a significant event in the history of Australia. It was a major event in the Australian gold rushes and the Australian gold mining industry. The first gold rush in Australia began in May 1851 after prospector Edward Hargraves claimed to have found payable gold in the Bathurst region of New South Wales. The gold rush attracted thousands of immigrants from other countries, including China, and led to the establishment of the Australian colonies of New South Wales, Victoria, Queensland, South Australia, Western Australia, and Tasmania.
